webpackJsonp([82894691907034],{391:function(e,o){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>\n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 1600px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 66.6092943201377%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="looking smug"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/looking-smug-e403b02c28c328ab256648e43f72afa5-ee623.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/looking-smug-e403b02c28c328ab256648e43f72afa5-51a12.jpg 400w,\n/static/looking-smug-e403b02c28c328ab256648e43f72afa5-b1745.jpg 800w,\n/static/looking-smug-e403b02c28c328ab256648e43f72afa5-ee623.jpg 1600w,\n/static/looking-smug-e403b02c28c328ab256648e43f72afa5-748d4.jpg 2400w,\n/static/looking-smug-e403b02c28c328ab256648e43f72afa5-ac5fa.jpg 3200w,\n/static/looking-smug-e403b02c28c328ab256648e43f72afa5-a6104.jpg 4800w,\n/static/looking-smug-e403b02c28c328ab256648e43f72afa5-809dd.jpg 5229w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </p>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class="gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"\n            style="padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;"\n          >\n            <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/119031210" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen="" mozallowfullscreen="" allowfullscreen style="\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          "></iframe>\n<p><a href="https://vimeo.com/119031210">squarepusher</a> from <a href="https://vimeo.com/owentrueblood">Owen Trueblood</a> on <a href="https://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</p>\n          </div>\n          </div>\n<br>\n<h2>Driving an LED Array from Shaders Running on a Raspberry Pi</h2>\n<p>The Very Large LED Array, or VLLA for short, is a bunch of LEDs mounted on a 4x8\'\nsheet of plywood driven by two Teensy microcontrollers and a Raspberry Pi. The\nhardware was designed and <a href="https://e2e.ti.com/group/universityprogram/students/m/students_repository/664650" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">constructed by friends of mine</a>\nfor our hall in our dorm at MIT with funding from Texas Instruments. The goal was\nto create an impressive light show for parties.</p>\n<p>I was interested in the software driving the display and had a desperate need to\nobsess over something not school related at the end of my 2nd semester in my\njunior year, so I developed a series of tools for creating effects for the display.\nIn its final form the system could run effects written in JavaScript or Lua, piped\nframe-by-frame over UDP, read from GIFs, or streamed from pixels on a Linux desktop.</p>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class="gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"\n            style="padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;"\n          >\n            <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/117706820" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen="" mozallowfullscreen="" allowfullscreen style="\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          "></iframe>\n<p><a href="https://vimeo.com/117706820">doctor</a> from <a href="https://vimeo.com/owentrueblood">Owen Trueblood</a> on <a href="https://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</p>\n          </div>\n          </div>\n<br>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class="gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"\n            style="padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;"\n          >\n            <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/117706817" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen="" mozallowfullscreen="" allowfullscreen style="\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          "></iframe>\n<p><a href="https://vimeo.com/117706817">madeon</a> from <a href="https://vimeo.com/owentrueblood">Owen Trueblood</a> on <a href="https://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</p>\n          </div>\n          </div>\n<br>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class="gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"\n            style="padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;"\n          >\n            <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/119031212" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen="" mozallowfullscreen="" allowfullscreen style="\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          "></iframe>\n<p><a href="https://vimeo.com/119031212">flutebox</a> from <a href="https://vimeo.com/owentrueblood">Owen Trueblood</a> on <a href="https://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</p>\n          </div>\n          </div>\n<br>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class="gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"\n            style="padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;"\n          >\n            <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/119031211" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen="" mozallowfullscreen="" allowfullscreen style="\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          "></iframe>\n<p><a href="https://vimeo.com/119031211">roland</a> from <a href="https://vimeo.com/owentrueblood">Owen Trueblood</a> on <a href="https://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</p>\n          </div>\n          </div>\n<br>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class="gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"\n            style="padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;"\n          >\n            <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/117706819" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen="" mozallowfullscreen="" allowfullscreen style="\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          "></iframe>\n<p><a href="https://vimeo.com/117706819">cats-on-mars</a> from <a href="https://vimeo.com/owentrueblood">Owen Trueblood</a> on <a href="https://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</p>\n          </div>\n          </div>\n<br>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class="gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"\n            style="padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;"\n          >\n            <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/117706818" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen="" mozallowfullscreen="" allowfullscreen style="\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          "></iframe>\n<p><a href="https://vimeo.com/117706818">beats-around-madison</a> from <a href="https://vimeo.com/owentrueblood">Owen Trueblood</a> on <a href="https://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</p>\n          </div>\n          </div>\n<br>\n<h2>Rotating a Panda</h2>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class="gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"\n            style="padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;"\n          >\n            <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/110753715" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen="" mozallowfullscreen="" allowfullscreen style="\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          "></iframe>\n<p><a href="https://vimeo.com/110753715">Panda LED Effect Demo</a> from <a href="https://vimeo.com/owentrueblood">Owen Trueblood</a> on <a href="https://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</p>\n          </div>\n          </div>\n<br>\n<p>One of the first effects I developed for the VLLA was directly inspired by a\nloading screen in a demo by Fairlight called We Are New. In the demo a\npistol-wielding panda rendered in chunky volumetric form rotated in 3D space.</p>\n<p>You can find my code to recreate the effect below:</p>\n<script src="https://gist.github.com/jmptable/a159de1ec2ed6620939e73e7d51793ac.js"></script>\n<br>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class="gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"\n            style="padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;"\n          >\n            <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/L8onlB0F1_A?rel=0&amp;start=311" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen style="\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          "></iframe>\n          </div>\n          </div>',frontmatter:{title:"The Very Large LED Array",date:"10.12.2014",description:"A 64x32 LED display with a livecoding interface",cover:{publicURL:"/static/looking-smug-e403b02c28c328ab256648e43f72afa5.jpg",childImageSharp:{resize:{src:"/static/looking-smug-e403b02c28c328ab256648e43f72afa5-648b2.jpg"}}}},fields:{slug:"/the-very-large-led-array"},excerpt:"Driving an LED Array from Shaders Running on a Raspberry Pi The Very Large LED Array, or VLLA for short, is a bunch of LEDs mounted on a 4x…"}},pathContext:{slug:"/the-very-large-led-array"}}}});
